claim.claim-text:
1. An engine control apparatus comprising:
a turbo-supercharger driven by exhaust energy of an engine in a vehicle;
an EGR (Exhaust Gas Recirculation) path interconnecting an exhaust path and an inlet path of the engine;
an EGR valve for adjusting the flow rate of air passing through said EGR path;
a deceleration condition detector for detecting deceleration of the vehicle;
a fuel reduction control unit for reducing the rate of fuel injection when deceleration of the vehicle is detected;
an inlet throttle valve in the inlet path, and
